#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.94:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Asuravagga"
msgstr "10. Demons"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Tatiyasamādhisutta"
msgstr "94. Immersion (3rd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.94"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.94:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an4.94:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.94:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na "
"lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya."
msgstr ""
"One person has internal serenity of heart, but not the higher wisdom of "
"discernment of principles."

msgctxt "an4.94:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, "
"na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa."
msgstr ""
"One person has the higher wisdom of discernment of principles, but not "
"internal serenity of heart."

msgctxt "an4.94:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ceva lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ "
"cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya."
msgstr ""
"One person has neither internal serenity of heart, nor the higher wisdom of "
"discernment of principles."

msgctxt "an4.94:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ "
"cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya."
msgstr ""
"One person has both internal serenity of heart, and the higher wisdom of "
"discernment of principles."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.94:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na lābhī "
"adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī "
"adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"As for the person who has serenity but not discernment: they should approach "
"someone who has discernment and ask:"

msgctxt "an4.94:2.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā?"
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should conditions be seen?"

msgctxt "an4.94:2.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā?"
msgstr "How should they be comprehended?"

#. VAR: vipassitabbā → passitabbā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.94:2.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti?"
msgstr "How should they be discerned?’"

msgctxt "an4.94:2.5"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr "That person would answer from their own experience:"

msgctxt "an4.94:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ "
"saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is how conditions should be seen, comprehended, and discerned.’"

msgctxt "an4.94:2.7"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca "
"adhipaññādhammavipassanāya."
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.94:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya na lābhī "
"ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī "
"ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"As for the person who has discernment but not serenity: they should approach "
"someone who has serenity and ask:"

msgctxt "an4.94:3.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled?"

#. VAR: sannisādetabbaṃ → sanniyādetabbaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.94:3.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ?"
msgstr "How should it be settled?"

#. VAR: cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ → ekodikattabbaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.94:3.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ?"
msgstr "How should it be unified?"

msgctxt "an4.94:3.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti?"
msgstr "How should it be immersed in samādhi?’"

msgctxt "an4.94:3.6"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr "That person would answer from their own experience:"

msgctxt "an4.94:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ "
"cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and "
"immersed in samādhi.’"

msgctxt "an4.94:3.8"
msgid ""
"So aparena samaye lābhī ceva hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya lābhī ca "
"ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa."
msgstr "After some time they have both discernment and serenity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.95"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.94:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ceva lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na "
"ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ "
"puggalo lābhī ceva ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca "
"adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"As for the person who has neither serenity nor discernment: they should "
"approach someone who has serenity and discernment and ask:"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled?"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ?"
msgstr "How should it be settled?"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ?"
msgstr "How should it be unified?"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ?"
msgstr "How should it be immersed in samādhi?’"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.6"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā?"
msgstr "How should conditions be seen?"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.7"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā?"
msgstr "How should they be comprehended?"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.8"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti?"
msgstr "How should they be discerned?’"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.9"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr "That person would answer as they’ve seen and known:"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.10"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ "
"cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ, evaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, "
"evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and "
"immersed in samādhi. And this is how conditions should be seen, "
"comprehended, and discerned.’"

msgctxt "an4.94:4.11"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca "
"adhipaññādhammavipassanāya."
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.94:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa "
"lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena tesu ceva "
"kusalesu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya uttari āsavānaṃ khayāya yogo karaṇīyo."
msgstr ""
"As for the person who has both serenity and discernment: grounded on those "
"skillful qualities, they should practice meditation further to end the "
"defilements."

msgctxt "an4.94:5.2"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti."
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.94:5.3"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
